{
  "stem": "1419.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] when we came to Rabka, we were still-- our, our hometown was still not evacuated.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In other words, my mother and my, my sister and my, my grandfather were still living in Nowy Targ.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were just sent to Rabka.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was 17.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I came to Rabka, and, and we worked.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we worked very hard.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were known in Rabka, if you don't work, if they catch you, they see you not working, you get killed, which, which did happen quite a few times.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were working in, in forest, and, and all of a sudden, you know, some, some, some people stopped for a minute, not-- stopped working.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And all of a sudden from behind the, the trees came a-- came a Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he killed him right on the spot.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It happened quite often.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I didn't see it, but I knew about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But it happened in 1942.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I never came back to Poland when there, there, there was the big selection in Poland.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In other words, the, the last day of, of, of the-- of the Jews from Nowy Targ.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was September 1st, [BACKGROUND NOISE] 1942.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I never seen my, my mother and, and sisters again.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We were in Rabka, and that day in, in Nowy Targ, they, they took all the Jews on the [GERMAN] they called it, on the-- on the-- on the-- not too far from the rail station.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They took all the Jews then, and they took all the Judenrat and all, all these people which they couldn't work.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They took them all on the trucks-- or I don't know-- on the trucks or they walked them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They took them to the cemetery and they killed them.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
